<HEADER>
A7954 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBC-USC-LADN     12-14 0440
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-USC-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HACKETT TO REVIEW STAFF
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Although he ``doesn't foresee changes,'' USC coach
Paul Hackett said he intends to evaluate his coaching staff soon
after the Trojans play Texas Christian in the Sun Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   Hackett nearly lost defensive coordinator Bill Young to Hawaii
last week, but what about the possibility he might decide to alter
his staff?
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not saying I would never make a change, but I don't
foresee changes,'' Hackett said. ``As the season comes to a close
after the bowl game, I will sit down with everybody and talk. I go
through an evaluation process.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is an emotional job. Every year, you evaluate every
aspect of the program. It's the same thing with coaches.''
</P>
<P>
   Few within the program expect offensive coordinator Hue Jackson
to return next season, although no decisions have been made yet.
Although Jackson called the plays in the second half of the Notre
Dame game, he has relinquished play calling to Hackett for almost
the entire season.
</P>
<P>
   ``If a guy wants to better himself, I would let him pursue
that,'' Hackett said. ``Anybody interested in a job has my
blessing.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Strong safety?: Freshman tailback Frank Strong has
contemplated moving over to defense, perhaps to the secondary, but
intends to remain on offense at least through the end of the
season.
</P>
<P>
   ``To change positions would show a lack of confidence,'' Strong
said. ``I feel pretty good about tailback right now. I feel my
heart is at tailback.''
</P>
<P>
   Strong's playing time reduced dramatically after he fumbled
twice against Florida State and once against California.
</P>
<P>
   __ Ready for a break: Tailback Chad Morton will enjoy having
this week off because he will finally get a chance to rest his sore
ankle, which has bothered him since the Stanford game in early
November.
</P>
<P>
   ``My ankle is still sore once in awhile,'' Morton said. ``This
week will be good for it.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Change in schedule: The Trojans will hold a light practice
Friday, then hold a regular practice Saturday. Originally, they
were supposed to be off the entire week and resume practicing
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   __ Welch cleared: Offensive tackle Matt Welch has been cleared
again to practice, after suffering a rapid heart beat during the
Notre Dame game. It's believed to be a pre-existing condition that
he also experienced at Santa Ana JC.
</P>
<P>
   __ Sanford stays: Former USC assistant coach Mike Sanford, now
the quarterbacks coach at Notre Dame, has turned down the offensive
coordinator's position at Nevada-Las Vegas.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
