<P>
   Police Searches Curbed
</P>
<P>
   When the Supreme Court weighs the competing interests of the
police and ordinary citizens these days, the police usually come
out ahead. So a decision that a speeding ticket does not
automatically allow the police to search a car was notable.
</P>
<P>
   The justices overturned a ruling by the Supreme Court in Iowa,
where a law authorized police to conduct a full-blown search
whenever they issue a traffic ticket.
</P>
<P>
   The 1983 law was the only one of its kind in the country, but
had the court upheld it, the idea would undoubtedly have spread.
Chief Justice William Rehnquist said there was no justification for
the search; once a driver is stopped for speeding, he said, all the
necessary evidence of the offense has been obtained.
</P>
