<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-R-REVIEW-BUDGET-NYT </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Editors: The following items from The N.Y. Times Week in Review
for Sunday, Dec. 13, moved Saturday in the `a' category (unless
otherwise noted) and are repeated Monday.
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-REVIEW (Washington) _ Nothing about an impeachment trial
would be logical, by ordinary legal standards. It would be part law
and part politics, governed partly by the Constitution, partly by
ancient Senate rules and partly by the seat of the pants. An
in-depth look at what to expect in such a trial. By David E.
Rosenbaum. WITH GRAPHIC.
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-JACKSON-REVIEW (Undated) _ The president's refrain today
is: Don't impeach me; censure me. But back in 1834, the argument
was the other way around: Don't censure me; impeach me. A look at
Andrew Jackson's argument against presidential censure.
</P>
<P>
   TOYS-KIDS-REVIEW (Undated) _ America's children are being buried
in an avalanche of toys. It's partly a function of demographics:
There are fewer children and more adults to dote on them. Fueling
the trend are TV's ceaseless shilling of merchandise, guilt on the
part of working, often absentee parents, clevermarketing of toys as
learning tools, and the inescapable realization that a kid
transfixed by a toy is a kid temporarily not bothering a parent.
Now some professionals fear children are being simultaneously
overstimulated and desensitized by a deluge of misguided love. By
Douglas Martin.
</P>
<P>
   BOYS-WOES-REVIEW (Undated) _ It's getting harder and harder to
be a boy. No one's calling for affirmative action for boys just
yet. But given the fact that girls are becoming an ever-larger
majority at most American colleges, many educators are beginning to
think that boys should get more attention. By Tamar Lewin.
</P>
<P>
   ATLANTA-DRIVETHRU-REVIEW (Atlanta) _ A look at a proposed
ordinance to ban the construction of new drive-through windows in
Atlanta, the national leader in `autodependency.' Under thes bill,
the city would effectively declare an end to more convenient but
bloodless car-bound transactions at banks, fast-food eateries, dry
cleaners, pharmacies, liquor stores and cappucino cafes. By Kevin
Sack.
</P>
<P>
   INDEPENDENT-COUNSELS-REVIEW (Undated) _ Complaints about the
independent counsel law are coming at a critical time: The statute
is due to expire next year, and Democrats and Republicans are
lining to up declare that, after two decades, the law intended to
keep politics out of corruption cases should be allowed to die. By
David Johnston. WITH GRAPHIC.
</P>
<P>
   ORGAN-DONORS-REVIEW (Undated) _ Organs: The ultimate gifts.
Studies show that donors fare quite well with a single kidney, and
that their life spans are not shortened. But when a relative needs
an organ, the potential for subtle and not-so-subtle coercion on a
donor in the immediate family is so great that some doctors feel
compelled to offer that member an out, sometimes giving the
impression that the potential donor is not a good match. By David
Stryker.
</P>
<P>
   SPAIN-LATIN-REVIEW (Undated) _ Spain served as a model for its
former Latin American colonies in its transition from dictatorship
to democracy by starting off on a clean slate without
recriminations for the past. Now though, in attempting to put
Chile's ex-dictator Pinochet on trial, Spain is trying to do to
Chile what it did not do to itself. By Alan Riding. (moved in `i'
category).
</P>
<P>
   MAFIA-REVIEW (Undated) _ Today's bookshelves are crowded with
self-help books from celebrated tycoons. If one had been written by
the infamous Mafia boss Charles `Lucky' Luciano (who was recently
honored as one of Time magazine's most influential business
geniuses of the century), here are some of the lessons it might
contain. By Joe Sharkey.
</P>
<P>
   SINATRA-BOBBYSOXERS-REVIEW (Undated) _ An FBI report from 1946
about Frank Sinatra's rapturous effect on teen-age girls.
</P>
<P>
   AIR-GRIDLOCK-REVIEW (New York) _ Gridlock in the wild blue
yonder: a look at air traffic congestion in the skies over New
York. By Matthew L. Wald. WITH GRAPHIC.
</P>
<P>
   THISWEEK-REVIEW (Undated) _ Some highlights of the week.
</P>
<P>
