good a car or cat is, both start reaching their design limits after
about 15 years. And that's why I found myself sadly walking from a
junkyard recently after selling out a faithful, 15-year-old,
198,000-mile car. (Lane, Cox News Service) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   EZZARD-COLUMN _ ATLANTA _ The only whistle that might stop the
House impeachment train _ the zealots' express _ is corporate
America. Wall Street. When business talks, Republicans listen.
(Ezzard, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   KABAT-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ Many years ago when we were
house-hunting, our real estate agent picked us up in her new car to
show us some houses. After we got into her car, we heard a robotic
voice say ``Your door is ajar. Your door is ajar.'' Alarmed, we
shut the door. ``Thank you,'' came the tinny voice. That was our
first experience with ``talking cars.'' It also was our last. I
don't want my car to talk to me. If I have to resort to having
conversations with a vehicle, I need to check into the nearest
chapter of Get-A-Life Anonymous. (Kabat, Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
