<P>
   TECHTOOLS _ ATLANTA _ To conclude our look at the latest crop of
electronic encyclopedias, we'll take a very brief glance at the
1999 DVD version of the Encarta reference suite, and then move on
to some other encylopedic sorts of things. Basically, the DVD
reference suite is nothing more than the Deluxe Encarta plus
Microsoft's very useful Bookshelf and the Visual Globe. The trick,
of course, is that material which takes up five ordinary CD-ROMs is
here presented on one _ with more multimedia thrown in for good
measure.(Warner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   CYBERSCENE _ ATLANTA _ The trouble with the Internet these days
is that it's so danged practical. Not only can you check out the
weather at your holiday destination, an online roadmap can show you
how to get there. (Husted, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   TECHNOBUDDY _ ATLANTA _ It probably shouldn't work this way but
_ at this time of the year _ almost everything has a price tag on
it. If you are like me, your credit cards have already worked so
hard they're developing muscles. That's why we'll spend today
looking at my favorite kind of computer software _ free stuff.
(Husted, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
