   SCIENCE/MEDICINE
</P>
<P>
   STAR _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Genesis has one version of creation,
astronomy another. Astronomy says we all come from a supernova, a
star whose explosion seeded what became Earth and us with calcium,
carbon, and the 101 other chemical elements in the sun, the planets
and our bodies. A University of Texas astronomer, on the trail of
our ancestor supernova, believe they've found a solid clue: a
unique star in the halo around the Milky Way that may have been the
first recipient of the supernova's seeding. (Stanley, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED SUNDAY
