<SLUG> BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`MADELINE' IS FAMILY FUN; `LETHAL WEAPON 4' SO-SO 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Madeline'' _ This live-action version of the
French schoolgirl's adventures retains the impish qualities of the
original stories. Wonderfully cast and exquisitely produced, this
one is a great holiday film for the entire family.
</P>
<P>
   ``Lethal Weapon 4'' _ Aren't Mel Gibson and Danny Glover getting
a little long in the tooth for this sort of action series? The
acting is predictable, the stunts acceptable, and it does mark the
screen debut of comic Chris Rock, but there's little to recommend
it.
</P>
<P>
   ``Halloween H20'' _ Why don't they just take Freddie Krueger of
``Elm Street,'' Jason of ``Friday the 13th,'' and Michael Myers of
this series into a nuclear waste dump? Jamie Lee Curtis is back,
some 20 years after John Carpenter's original, but that's not
enough.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Strauss Family'' _ Great music provided by the London
Symphony Orchestra, but the family is reduced to palatable
stereotypes in this overwrought melodrama.
</P>
<P>
   ``Indiscreet'' _ Not to be confused with the Hitchcock film,
this one stars Adam Baldwin, Luke Perry, and Gloria Reuben as a
treacherous triangle. Same-old, same-old.
</P>
<P>
   ``A Christmas Story'' _ Bob Clark's terrific film based on Jean
Shepherd's tales of growing up Midwestern takes its place alongside
more traditional Christmas films. Funny, touching, and smart.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: Dec. 18: ``Summer of the Monkeys.'' Dec. 22:
``Cousin Bette,'' ``Blade,'' ``The Secret of NIMH 2,'' ``Billy's
Hollywood Screen Kiss,'' ``Random Encounter,'' ``The Rat Pack,''
``Elective Affinities,'' ``Act of War.'' Dec. 29: ``The Avengers,''
``Why Do Fools Fall in Love,'' ``Montana,'' ``Knock Off,''
``Baseketball.'' Jan. 5: ``Out of Sight,'' ``The Rescuers,'' ``How
Stella Got Her Groove Back,'' ``Every Mother's Fear,'' ``Dr. Who:
The Mind of Evil,'' ``Disturbing Behavior,'' ``Project Grizzly,''
``Scarred City.'' Jan. 12: ``Wilde,'' ``Love and Death on Long
Island,'' ``The Truman Show,'' ``Our Mutual Friend,'' ``p,''
``Dance With Me,'' ``Henry Fool,'' ``Fireworks,'' ``Sing and Dance
with Barney,'' ``Wubbulous World of Dr. Seuss.'' Jan. 19: ``Smoke
Signals,'' ``Invasion Earth,'' ``Mafia!,'' ``Because of Him,''
``The Amazing Mrs. Holliday,'' ``Slums of Beverly Hills,''
``Evidence of Blood,'' ``Buffalo Island,'' ``Little City,''
``Buffalo 66.'' Jan. 26: ``Kurt and Courtney,'' ``Whatever,''
``Cube,'' ``Rush Hour.'' Feb. 2: ``There's Something About Mary,''
``Brute Force,'' ``Shooting Fish,'' ``Naked City,'' ``The Blue
Gardenia.'' Feb. 9: ``The Invasion Begins.''
</P>
</TEXT>
