<HEADLINE>
GLOBE CRITICS RATE FILMS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
 ! poor, !! fair, !!! good, !!!! excellent  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   !!! 1/2 ``A Simple Plan'' A dark, impressively crafted morality
fable. Farm-town brothers Bill Paxton and Billy Bob Thornton (and
the latter's redneck sidekick, Brent Briscoe) find a duffel bag of
dirty money that creates as many problems as it solves. Terrific
acting and primal foreboding in this starkly rendered stretch for
all involved, including director Sam Raimi. (R)
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   !! 1/2 ``Somewhere in the City'' An entertaining if somewhat
disjointed look into the cluttered lives and loves of six New
Yorkers living in a tenement on the fabulously seedy Lower East
Side, with Sandra Bernhard in her best role since 1983's ``The King
of Comedy.'' (Unrated) (Renee Graham)
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (FR) !!! ``Star Trek: Insurrection'' A surefooted but far from
trailblazing ninth installment. Patrick Stewart's stalwart Captain
Picard leads his team to a planet that looks like a hippie
paradise, where Brant Spiner's Data runs amok and a prunelike race
of troublemakers tries to subvert the Federation's hands-off edict
regarding locals. (PG)
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   !!! ``Lenny Bruce: Swear To Tell the Truth'' Robert B. Weide's
sympathetic profile of the controversial comic makes a strong case
that Bruce was done in by political forces dedicated to the status
quo. And Bruce, of course, was as far from the status quo as he
could get. What killed him in the end was that his act wasn't an
act at all: He meant every dirty word. (Unrated) (Michael Blowen)
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   !!! 1/2 ``Waking Ned Devine'' Light, charming Irish comedy in
which a whole village gets in on a scam to cash in a dead man's
winning lottery ticket. David Kelly and Ian Bannen lead the
larcenous, blarney-filled procession in this film, which updates
such predecessors as ``Local Hero'' and ``Tight Little Island''
with geezer-powered larceny. (PG)
</P>
</TEXT>
