<P>
   IMPEACH-MODERATES (Washington) _ Developments among moderates
whose votes on impeachment are pivotal. By James Dao.
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-DEMS (Washington) _ We talk to those Democrats who have
declared themselves in favor of impeachment about why they're
breaking ranks. By Frank Bruni.
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-MAIL (Washington) _ Members of Congress are being
swamped with constituent calls, faxes, e-mails. Where it is coming
from and what it means. By Katharine Q. Seelye.
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-RODINO (Undated) _ Peter Rodino, who led the Judiciary
Committee during Watergate, is angry because he thinks what is
going on is not for the good of the country. And he doesn't like
Chairman Hyde's handling of all this, either. By David M.
Halbfinger.
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-GORE (Washington) _ With the vice president as he
announces a law enforcement initiative with Attorney General Reno.
By Adam Nagourney.
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-RADIO (Undated) _ What talk radio is saying about the
president and Congress. By Terry Pristin.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; OTHER WASHINGTON &LR;  (``w'' code)
</P>
<P>
   SCOTUS (Washington) _ A roundup: The Supreme Court unanimously
rules that it violates federal civil rights law to dismiss somebody
in retaliation for testifying in a Federal criminal trial; other
cases. By Linda Greenhouse.
</P>
<P>
   AUTO-POLLUTION (Washington) _ A dozen state environmental
officials come to town to lobby the EPA for tougher standards on
automobile tailpipe emissions and on sulfur in gasoline, two major
disputed rules that the administration is debating. (700 words)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL GENERAL &LR;  (``a'' code)
</P>
<P>
   TOBACCO-LAWYER (Undated) _ How one tobacco lawyer, fearing that
his fees would be slashed because of an overall cap on payments,
pumped up his bill from $50 million in hopes of getting a bigger
piece of the pie. By Barry Meier.
</P>
<P>
   PUERTORICO-ASSESS (San Juan, P.R.) _ An analysis of Sunday's
``none of the above'' vote that backed the status quo in Puerto
Rico. By Mireya Navarro.
</P>
<P>
   FUNDRAISING-CHUNG (Los Angeles) _ Johnny Chung, the Democratic
fund raiser, is sentenced in Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL &LR;  (``i'' code)
</P>
<P>
   MIDEAST-CLINTON (Gaza City, Gaza Strip) _ Ledeall: President
Clinton goes to Gaza, Palestinians approve charter changes, a
Clinton-Netanyahu-Arafat meeting possible later today or Tuesday.
By Deborah Sontag.
</P>
<P>
   With map.
</P>
<P>
   MIDEAST-SCENE (Gaza City) _ A color story on the Clinton visit
to Gaza. By James Bennet.
