   _ Most women know that taking 400 micrograms of folic acid early
in pregnancy can reduce the risk of their babies having certain
birth defects of the brain and spine. But a new survey conducted by
the March of Dimes warns that most women take that B vitamin too
late in pregnancy to be effective. (240 words)
</P>
<P>
   _ When air passengers are hunkered down in their economy seats
the consequences can be far more serious than a crick in the neck,
stiff muscles, swollen ankles or an aching back. The shrinking
space between seats can trap the legs and restrict movement,
triggering blood clots. Experts offer tips on dealing with it. (320
words)
