<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients)  
. 
The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following stories
today for use by NYTimes News Service clients. They will move in
the ``e'' entertainment news file. For questions, contact Jimmy
Johnson at the Daily News, (818) 713-3695. 
. 
DEVINE-MOVIE (Los Angeles) _ After lifetimes of hard work, the two
senior citizens saw their chance to hit it big and, despite the
great risk involved, took it. That's the plotline for ``Waking Ned
Devine,'' the English-Irish lottery scam comedy that's become one
of the season's most popular specialty movies. But the same applies
to the film's two stars, 70-year-old Ian Bannen and 69-year-old
David Kelly, acting veterans who are finally experiencing a bit of
well-deserved stardom. By Bob Strauss. 
. 
KROQ-CONCERT (Los Angeles) _ `It's All Been Done,'' sang Toronto's
Barenaked Ladies, perhaps summing up today's rock scene in the
title of one of their hits Friday during the opening night of
KROQ's pair of 9th annual Almost Acoustic Christmas shows at the
Shrine Auditorium. By Fred Shuster. 
. 

