their witness, hundreds of former Palestinian terrorists voted here
Monday to rid their organization's charter of any clauses calling
for the destruction of Israel, knocking down a critical roadblock
on the rutted path to peace. By Deborah Sontag. With map.
</P>
<P>
   MIDEAST-SCENE (Gaza City) _ The band left something to be
desired. The honor guard could have been criser and more precise.
But from the immense American and Palestinian flags draped from the
airport's control tower to the joint appearance by two leaders at
which reporters shouted questions about impeachment, the day had
all the feel of a typical state visit by President Clinton. Yet one
thing was, of course, missing: the state. By James Bennet.
</P>
<P>
   U.N.-ANNAN (United Nations) _ Secretary General Kofi Annan, in
interview, distances himself from U.S. policy on Iraq. By Barbara
Crossette.
