medical and lawyer groups who filed fraudulent claims in allegedly
staging car accidents in Houston and Dallas. The suit in Dallas
says that the groups were responsible for 153 collisions resulting
in fraudulent claims of $2 million. In Houston, 199 rear-end
collisions were staged with fraudulent claims of $2.8 million.
(Golz, Austin American-Statesman).
