<HEADER>
A9261 &Cx1f; tad-z
u f &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBN-GREENE-COX     12-14 0226
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-GREENE-COX </SLUG>

<TEXT>
<P>
   Panthers' Greene suspended, fined $117,647
</P>
<P>
   By Len Pasquarelli
</P>
<P>
   C. 1998 Cox News Service
</P>
<P>
   His hands were around the neck of assistant coach Kevin Steele,
but Carolina Panthers linebacker Kevin Greene insisted Monday that
his Sunday stranglehold should not be compared to the actions of
NBA forward Latrell Sprewell last year.
</P>
<P>
   ``No way,'' said Greene, who was suspended for one game by coach
Dom Capers, a penalty that will cost the 14-year veteran $117,647.
``This was strictly a heat-of-the-moment kind of thing. That guy
came back two times on his coach.''
</P>
<P>
   The embarrassing sideline scuffle early in the second quarter is
the latest indiscretion for a Panthers team that has suffered
through a tough season on and off the field. Greene apparently
missed a defensive call and remained on the periphery instead of
blitzing inside.
</P>
<P>
   Steele, the team's linebackers coach, was complaining to the
entire defense and Greene felt the criticism was directly only at
him. ``Get out my face,'' he screamed at Steele as he rose off the
bench to confront the coach.
</P>
<P>
   Cornerback Eric Davis and outside linebackers coach Billy Davis
separated the two but not before the action was captured by still
and television cameras.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-12-14-98 1822EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
