<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Timeline for Dan Reeves' heart surgery
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   November _ Falcons coach Dan Reeves begins experiencing chest
pains but doesn't relay the information to any doctors or assistant
coaches.
</P>
<P>
   1-4 p.m. Sunday _ While on the sideline during a 27-17 victory
over the New Orleans Saints, Reeves experiences chest pains and a
burning sensation in his chest and the back of his throat.
</P>
<P>
   4:20 p.m. Sunday _ After the game, Reeves explains his symptoms
to Dr. Charlie Harrison, one of the team's physicians.
</P>
<P>
   5:15 p.m. Sunday _ Reeves jokes with players while boarding the
team's charter back to Atlanta, handing out pastries. Free safety
Eugene Robinson tussles his hair, ``to loosen him up,'' teammate
Cornelius Bennett says.
</P>
<P>
   6 p.m. Sunday _ Reeves confers on the plane with Harrison, and
the two discuss options. It is agreed that he will undergo an
angiogram the next morning in Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   6:30 a.m. Monday _ Reeves checks into Piedmont hospital, and
when dye is inserted into arteries in his heart via
catheterization, none passes through one artery, indicating a
complete, or nearly complete, blockage. So little passes through
two others that it is determined he has at least an 80 percent
blockage in them.
</P>
<P>
   11:30 a.m. Monday _ Reeves undergoes quadruple heart bypass
surgery at Piedmont with cardiac surgeon James Kauten in charge.
Veins are grafted from the inside of his legs and from behind the
pectoral muscles in his chest.
</P>
<P>
   3:30 p.m. Monday _ Surgery is over, and Reeves is moved into
intensive care, where his breathing is assisted by machine for
several hours until about 8 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
